Violence broke out at the presidential rally of the All Progressives Congress (APC) in Ogun state on Monday. The rally was brought to an abrupt end after Buhari raised the hand of Dapo Abiodun, the APC governorship candidate in the state. Immediately, the president raised Abiodun’s hand, some aggrieved persons threw objects towards his direction, forcing security operatives to form a ring around him. The aggrieved persons had earlier pelted Adams Oshiomhole, national chairman of the ruling party, with stones and chased supporters of Abiodun from the stadium.  More to follow… The supremacy battle within the Ogun State chapter of the All Progressives Congress (APC) came to the fore again yesterday when violence by rival members of the party marred the campaign rally of President Muhammadu Buhari in the state.   The venue of the rally, MKO Abiola International Stadium, Abeokuta,… In "Lead Stories" President Muhammadu Buhari has endorsed Dapo Abiodun as governorship candidate of the All Progressives Congress (APC) in the 2019 general election in Ogun State. The decision of the President came during his meeting on Friday with the former governor of Ogun State, and a chieftain of the All Progressives Congress,… In "News" The Arewa community in Ogun State yesterday vowed to deliver 300,000 votes for President Muhammadu Buhari and the All Progressives Congress (APC) governorship candidate in the state, Prince Dapo Abiodun, in 2019. The community, at its senatorial interactive meeting held in Abeokuta, promised to mobilise for a resounding victory for… In "News"